# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if the platform is not identical, it may cause problems.
#   Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Poetry uses pyproject.toml to manage dependencies and is recommended to be committed.
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   PDM stores project-wide configurations in .pdm.toml
.pdm.toml
#   pdm.lock is usually committed

# PEP 582 directory
__pypackages__/

